Method Detail

createAuthorization

ERSWSCreateAuthorizationResponse createAuthorization(ClientContext clientContext,
                                                     java.lang.String type,
                                                     java.lang.String purpose,
                                                     java.lang.String mimeType,
                                                     java.lang.String document,
                                                     ParameterMap parameters,
                                                     int timeout,
                                                     java.lang.String backURL)
Create an authorization token that a subscriber can authorize.
  • NAME user name
  • TERMINALID id of user device
  • SUBSCRIBERID personal number or customer id
  • SUBSCRIBERMSISDN phone number

Parameters:
clientContext - the client authentication context
type - type of request (signature, login or ...)
purpose - purpose of the authentication, eg "login", "applying for a bank account", etc
mimeType - mime-type of document text/html or text/plain
document - document as text-string
parameters - parameters as described
timeout - time before key becomes invalid.
backURL - (optional) URL for the app to launch after authorization is completed
Returns:
gives you a key and private/public qr code to use
Since:
2.2.0

queryAuthorization

ERSWSQueryAuthorizationResponse queryAuthorization(ClientContext clientContext,
                                                   java.lang.String key,
                                                   int progressTimeout)
Query (poll) for the authorization by the client of the token.

Parameters:
clientContext - the client authentication context
key - authorization token string
progressTimeout - response delay in seconds if pending (depends on server settings)
Returns:
information about the subscriber when status=SUCCESS, otherwise status is AUTHORIZATION_EXPIRED or AUTHORIZATION_CANCELLED or AUTHORIZATION_IN_PROGRESS
Since:
2.2.0

cancelAuthorization

Returns:

submitSubscriberAccount

ERSWSSubmitSubscriberAccountResponse submitSubscriberAccount(ClientContext context,
                                                             java.lang.String accountType,
                                                             ParameterMap parameters)
Add account to an existing subscriber (register an account).

Parameters in use:

  • ACCOUNT_ID account number
  • TERMINALID id of user device
  • KYC_REFERENCE type of authorization used
  • SUBSCRIBERID personal number or customer id
  • AUTHORIZATION_REFERENCE token

Parameters:
context - the client authentication context
registerType - What type of registration
parameters - Registration parameters, including account details
Returns:
report content
Since:
2.2.0
